<h2>Classification</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Layer.</strong> The handle ships <em>runnable code</em> → the impl is FUI
    (<code>webinjectors</code>/<code>webcontexts</code> plugs); WE keeps only the consume/provide
    <em>contract</em> shape. (Impl-is-not-a-standard / WE-holds-zero-impl.)</li>
  <li><strong>Fixed mechanic, not a configurable dimension.</strong> "Footgun or not" is not a pair of
    legitimate end-states to expose — only one branch is correct — so it is a fixed mechanic, ratified, not a
    dimension authors choose.</li>
  <li><strong>Most-permissive reading</strong> = the shape that makes the hang impossible (the restriction
    here removes a trap, it does not constrain a coherent use).</li>
  <li><strong>Native-first.</strong> The async iterator (<code>Symbol.asyncIterator</code>) is the
    platform-native reactive streaming primitive; reading the current value as a property mirrors Signals'
    <code>.get()</code>.</li>
</ul>

